0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-view","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header","style":{"background":"#fce7f3"},"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header-inner","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"back-btn","children":"← Back to Blog"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"blog-tag","style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","display":"inline-block"},"children":"Organization"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"blog-post-title","children":"How to Build a Desk Setup That Boosts Deep Focus"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":"May 22, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"5 min read"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-body","children":[["$","p","p-0",{"children":"Deep focus doesn't happen automatically. The environment you work in either supports it or fights it. Most desk setups — even expensive ones — are designed for how they look in a photo, not how they support hours of concentrated work."}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":"Here are the changes that have made the biggest difference in my own setup."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"1. Keep Only What's in Active Use on the Surface"}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":"Every object on your desk is a potential context switch. A phone within reach means you'll check it. A stack of papers means you'll shuffle through them when you hit a hard problem."}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":"The rule: if you haven't touched it today, it doesn't belong on the surface."}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":"This sounds extreme but it's not. Pens in a cup on the desk: yes. Spare chargers, sticky note pads, scissors: in a drawer or off the desk entirely."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"2. One Notebook, One Pen"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":["Multiple notebooks create decision overhead. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Which one does this go in?"}]," One notebook — kept open to the current page — removes that friction."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-6",{"children":"Same with pens. Pick one, keep it clipped to the notebook. When it runs out, replace it. Don't keep a cup of seventeen pens you rotate through."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"3. Position Your Monitor for Eye Level"}],"\n",["$","p","p-7",{"children":"Most people position their monitor too low. Looking down for hours creates neck tension that distracts from focus even when you don't consciously notice it."}],"\n",["$","p","p-8",{"children":"The top of the screen should be at or just below eye level. For laptop users, this means an external monitor or a laptop stand plus an external keyboard — the laptop screen alone is always too low."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"4. Get Cables Off the Surface"}],"\n",["$","p","p-9",{"children":"A tangled cable cluster is visual noise. Visual noise is a subtle but real attention drain. A simple cable management tray under the desk, or even a few cable clips along the desk edge, eliminates it."}],"\n",["$","p","p-10",{"children":"The goal isn't aesthetics for photos — it's removing things your eyes keep catching on."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-4",{"children":"5. Lighting on the Task, Not the Screen"}],"\n",["$","p","p-11",{"children":"A bright screen in a dark room causes eye strain within an hour. A desk lamp pointed at your notebook or keyboard — not at your screen — reduces that strain and signals to your brain that the desk is a working space."}],"\n",["$","p","p-12",{"children":"Warm light (2700–3000K) for evenings. Cooler daylight-balanced light (4000–5000K) for daytime focus work."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-5",{"children":"The Underlying Principle"}],"\n",["$","p","p-13",{"children":"A focus-optimized desk setup isn't about having the right products. It's about removing decisions and distractions from the space where decisions are supposed to be made. Every object that isn't earning its place on the surface is making focus harder."}],"\n","$L3"]}]]}],null,"$L4"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"CvsT0SS6A7kQnn3qWxvt7"}
3:["$","p","p-14",{"children":"Start with a clear desk and add things back only when you need them. You'll use less than you think."}]
